string can be created using
1)string
2)StringBuffer
3)StringBuilder

the diffrence b/w string and strinBuffer is that :
*string is immutable whereas stringBuffer is mutable.
e.g:->String name="krihsna";
           name.concat("chaitanya")--->this will create a new object and then it'll add finally giving us KrishnaChaitanya

********	but if we use StringBuffer*******
StringBuffer name="krishna";
name.append("chaitnaya");	//append():It is used to add text at the end of the exisistence text.
--->this will not create a new object and will add "chaitanya" directly to Krishna


when to use string biulder?
we use string builder like in the case of notepad where the string
frequently changes.

Syntax;->4 constructors
	Stringbiffer(){........}
	StringBuffer(CharSequence seq){.....}
	StringBuffer(String str){.........}
	StringBuffer(int capacity){..........}

ALL THE METHODS IN STRING BUFFER ARE SYNC.METHODS
